(121, 'Sashi Kumar', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/27/Sasikumar_02.jpg/220px-Sasikumar_02.jpg', 1, 'Sashi Kumar is a prominent media personality,from Kerala, India. He was the founder of Indiaâ€™s first regional satellite TV channel Asianet. He founded and chairs the Media Development Foundation, the not for profit public trust which set up and runs the prestigious Asian College of Journalism in Chennai. He was the first West Asia correspondent of The Hindu in the mid eighties. He directed the film Kaya Taran in Hindi based on the short story â€œWhen Big Trees Fallâ€ by writer N.S Madhavan.[1][2][3]', 0),
(122, 'Bala (actor)', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png', 1, 'Bala is an Indian film actor who mainly acts in Malayalam and Tamil films.[1] He acted in several Tamil films which were unsuccessful, and later entered Malayalam film industry, where his talent in smooth acting was quickly noted. His ease in bringing forth of facial expressions and his good physique helped him to be cast as both Hero and Villain in films and thus making him a formidable opponent to his colleagues like Prithviraj. He got the opportunity to work with big actors like Mohanlal and Mammootty and this has further helped polish his acting skills and become a chocolate hero among the', 0);
