(124, 'Ramya Krishnan', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d1/InterlanguageLinks-Asset-Pencil-Hover.gif', 1, 'Ramya Krishnan ([1] born 15 September 1967) is an actress who performs in Indian cinema. She has acted in over 200 films in five languages: Tamil, Telugu, Malayalam, Kannada and Hindi.', 0),
(125, 'Lakshmi Gopalaswamy', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3c/Lakshmi_Gopalaswamy_Thriller_Express_Asianet_Tour_Atlanata.jpg/220px-Lakshmi_Gopalaswamy_Thriller_Express_Asianet_Tour_Atlanata.jpg', 1, 'Lakshmi Gopalaswamy is a South Indian film actress and a classical dancer, qualified in Bharatanatyam.[1] She has acted in several Malayalam, Tamil, and Kannada films. Her debut Malayalam film Arayannangalude Veedu alongside Mammootty won her the Kerala State Film Award for the best supporting actress.[1] She was a judge on Asianetâ€™s dance show Vodafone Thakadhimi.[2]', 0),
(126, 'P. T. Kunju Muhammed', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/62/P_T_Kunjhimohammed_002.jpg/175px-P_T_Kunjhimohammed_002.jpg', 1, 'P. T. Kunju Muhammed (Malayalam: à´ªà´¿. à´Ÿà´¿. à´•àµà´žàµà´žàµà´®àµà´¹à´®àµà´®à´¦àµ) is a noted director and producer in Malayalam parallel film industry. Magrib was his first film venture.[1] He received a number of awards for his movies at the state level. He is a native of Chakkum Kandam near Chavakkad in Thrissur district, Kerala.[2]', 0),
(127, 'Kushboo Sundar', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/40/Kushboo-at-the-chennai-international-fashion-week-2.jpg/220px-Kushboo-at-the-chennai-international-fashion-week-2.jpg', 1, 'Nakhat Khan (born on 19 September 1970),[1] better known by her stage name Kushboo is an Indian actress, television hostess and producer.', 0),
(128, 'Parvati Melton', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Parvathi_Melton.jpg/220px-Parvathi_Melton.jpg', 1, 'Parvati Melton (born 7 January 1989[1]) is an Indian American actress and former model who mainly works in Telugu Film Industry. She appeared in several Telugu and Malayalam movies. She acted with Raja in the film Vennela, which turned out to be a success. She acted in the super hit Malayalam film Hallo with South Indian star Mohanlal.[2] She again shot to fame with item song in Telugu movie Dookudu opposite Mahesh Babu.[3]', 0),
(129, 'Allu Arjun', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d7/Allu-arjun.jpg/220px-Allu-arjun.jpg', 1, 'Allu Arjun (Telugu: à°…à°²à±à°²à± à°…à°°à±à°œà±à°¨à±; born 8 April 1983) is an Indian film actor known for his work in Telugu cinema. He has won two Nandi, two Filmfare and a CineMAA Award for his performances in Arya, Parugu and Vedam.', 0),
(130, 'Anuradha Mehta', 'http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.20wmf3/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4', 1, 'Anuradha Mehta (born 1981) is an Indian actress and former fashion model in the Kollywood and Tollywood industries.[1]', 0),
(131, '\n				Penmatsa Subbaraju\n			', 'http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.20wmf2/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4', 1, 'Penmatsa Subbaraju is an actor and fighter in Tollywood. He acted in many hit Tollywood films like Amma Nanna O Tamil Ammayi,Arya and Pokiri. He is currently trying to turn as a character artist from his fighter image.', 0),
(132, 'Sukumar', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png', 1, 'Sukumar Bandreddi (Telugu: à°¸à±à°•à±à°®à°¾à°°à± à°¬à±¦à°¡à±à°°à±†à°¡à±à°¡à°¿), better known by his first name, is a Tollywood film director and screenwriter. He worked as script associate and assistant director for the films Manasichi Choodu, Kshemanga Velli Labhanga Randi, Hanuman Junction and Dil, and made his directorial debut with Arya.', 0),
(133, 'Salim Kumar', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/46/Salimkumar.jpg/220px-Salimkumar.jpg', 1, 'Salim Kumar (Malayalam: à´¸à´²à´¿à´‚ à´•àµà´®à´¾à´°àµâ€; born on 10 June 1968) is a National Award-winning Indian film actor and mimic predominantly acting in Malayalam cinema.', 0),
(134, 'Katrina Kaif', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fc/Padlock-silver.svg/20px-Padlock-silver.svg.png', 1, 'Katrina Kaif (born 16 July 1984[2]) is a British Indian actress and former model who appears in Indian films, mainly in the Hindi-language film industry.[3][4] She has also appeared in Telugu and Malayalam films. She was voted the sexiest Asian woman in the world by Eastern Eye in the years 2008, 2009 and 2010.[5][6] Being a British citizen, she works in India on an employment visa.[1]', 0),
(135, 'I. V. Sasi', 'http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.20wmf3/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4', 1, 'Irruppam Veedu Sasidaran (Malayalam: à´‡à´°àµà´ªàµà´ªà´‚ à´µàµ€à´Ÿàµ à´¶à´¶à´¿à´§à´°àµ»), better known as I. V. Sasi, is a Malayali Indian film director who is known for his films of the 1970s, 80s and early 90s.', 0),
(136, 'Nikita Thukral', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/11/Nikita_Thukral_at_SRM_University_Milan_2010.jpg/220px-Nikita_Thukral_at_SRM_University_Milan_2010.jpg', 1, 'Nikita Thukral (born July 6, 1981) is an Indian film actress and model, who has acted in Telugu, Tamil, Kannada and Malayalam films. She is best known for her item number "Kodana Kodi" in Saroja.', 0),
(137, 'Jomon (director)', 'http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.20wmf3/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4', 1, 'Jomon is an Indian screenwriter and director who is actively involved in Malayalam cinema. After working as assistant director in films like Aalkkoottathil Thaniye, Uyarangalil, Adiyozhukkukal, 1921 and Douthyam, Jomon became independent director with the Mammootty starrer Samrajyam, which established new technical dimensions in Malayalam cinema. The film established Jomon as an happening director of Malayalam cinema. However he failed to give consistent hit films.', 0),
(138, 'Ashish Vidyarthi', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/db/Aashish_Vidyarthi.jpg/220px-Aashish_Vidyarthi.jpg', 1, 'Ashish Vidyarthi (born 19 June 1962) is an Indian actor who worked predominantly in Hindi films and lately in South Indian films. He has won the National Film Award for Best Supporting Actor for film Drohkaal in 1995.', 0),
(139, 'Meena (actress)', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png', 1, 'Meena Durairaj, (mononymously known as Meena, born in Chennai, Tamil Nadu, India) is a South Indian film and television actress. Meena debuted as a child artist in Telugu and Tamil films and has later starred in films produced by various regional industries. She is one of the most established actresses in the southern Indian film industry. In addition to acting, Meena is also a top model, singer, dancer, TV host and occasional dubbing artiste. At one time she was considered as the biggest south Indian actress by acting opposite Superstars of south India.', 0),
(140, 'Gopika', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2d/Gopika_2008.jpg/220px-Gopika_2008.jpg', 1, 'Gopika (born August 24, 1984[1][2] as Girly Anto) is an Indian film actress, who has predominantly starred in Malayalam films. Starting her career as a model, she ventured into acting with the film Pranayamanithooval (2003). She went on to appear in over 30 films, working in Tamil, Telugu and Kannada film industries as well.', 0),
(141, 'Prakash Raj', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/05/Prakashraj_Bhung.jpg/220px-Prakashraj_Bhung.jpg', 1, 'Prakash Rai (born 26 March 1965), better known by his stage name Prakash Raj, is a National Award winning film actor, director and producer who has worked in Kannada, Telugu, Tamil, Hindi and Malayalam films.He got introduced to films by K. Balachander in the movie Duet (1994). In remembrance, he named his production company "Duet Movies".[2][3]', 0),
(142, 'Major Ravi', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/Unbalanced_scales.svg/45px-Unbalanced_scales.svg.png', 1, 'Major A.K. Ravindran,[1] better known by his screen name Major Ravi is a former Indian Army Officer and a Malayali Indian filmmaker.', 0),
(143, 'Arjan Bajwa', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ec/Arjan_Bajwa-27_copy2.jpg/220px-Arjan_Bajwa-27_copy2.jpg', 1, 'Arjan Bajwa (Punjabi: à¨…à¨°à¨œà©à¨¨ à¨¬à¨¾à¨œà¨µà¨¾,Telugu: à°…à°°à±à°œà°¨à± à°¬à°¾à°œà±à°µ, Hindi: à¤…à¤°à¥à¤œà¤¨ à¤¬à¤œà¥à¤µ; born 3 September 1977) is an Indian actor who has acted in Telugu and Hindi films.[1]', 0),
(144, 'Tia Bajpai', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b0/Tia_bajpai.jpg/200px-Tia_bajpai.jpg', 1, 'Tia Bajpai (original name Twinkle Bajpai) is an Indian television and film actress. She was a finalist on the reality television music competition show, Sa Re Ga Ma Pa Challenge 2005. She was born in Lucknow, India.', 0),
(145, 'Urvashi (actress)', 'http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.20wmf3/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4', 1, 'Kavitha Ranjini, better known by her stage name Urvashi (Malayalam: à´‰àµ¼à´µà´¶à´¿), is an Indian film actress and producer. She was a prominent lead actress during the 1980s and 1990s in Malayalam, Tamil, Kannada, and Telugu films. She has dubbed in her own voice in all these languages. And she produced the film Pidakkozhi Koovunna Noottandu (1994). She won the National Film Award for Best Supporting Actress for her performance in Achuvinte Amma (2005).', 0),
(146, 'Harisree Ashokan', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/33/Harisree_Ashokan_2007.jpg/220px-Harisree_Ashokan_2007.jpg', 1, 'Harisree Ashokan (born December 28, 1964) is a Malayalam film actor who is known for his comedy roles. He has acted in more than 75 Malayalam films.', 0),
(147, 'Laila Mehdin', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1e/Indiafilm.svg/30px-Indiafilm.svg.png', 1, 'Laila Mehdin (born 24 October 1980) is an Indian actress. She has acted in Tamil, Telugu, Malayalam, Kannada and Hindi language films. She is probably best known for her critically acclaimed and award-winning performances in the Bala-directed films Nandha and Pithamagan.', 0),
(148, 'Jyothirmayi', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png', 1, 'Jyothirmayi is an Indian actress, model and television personality, who has primarily worked in Malayalam cinema. Starting her career in modelling, she ventured into television, working as an anchor and later starring in TV series. She went on to appear in feature films, gaining recognition for her critically acclaimed performance in Bhavam (2002) and her item number in Meesa Madhavan (2002).[1] Since, she has acted in nearly thirty films in Malayalam as well as in Tamil and Telugu language.[2]', 0),
(149, 'Roma Asrani', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/52/Roma.jpg/220px-Roma.jpg', 1, 'Roma Asrani (born August 25, 1984) is an Indian model-turned-actress who works mainly in Malayalam-language films. She made her dÃ©but in the Telugu film Mr. Errababu in 2005. She has acted in Tamil and Kannada films too.', 0),
(150, 'Parvathi Menon', 'http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.20wmf3/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4', 1, 'Parvathi Menon (Malayalam: à´ªà´¾à´°àµâ€à´µà´¤à´¿ à´®àµ‡à´¨àµ‹à´¨àµâ€}) is an Indian film actress who hails from Kerala. She made her debut in the Malayalam film Out of Syllabus in 2006.', 0),
(151, 'Vidharth', 'http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.20wmf3/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4', 1, 'Vidharth[1] is an Indian actor, primarily concentrating in Tamil films. He started his career in the year 2001 doing uncredited roles. His first major role was in Thiruvannamalai, where he played villain, but his next release Mynaa became a huge success. He has also done a film for AVM Productions titled Mudhal Idam. Currently he is working in Kollaikaran.', 0),
(152, 'Sanchita Shetty', 'http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.20wmf3/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4', 1, 'Sanchita Shetty is an Indian film actress, who has appeared in Kannada, Tamil and Telugu films.[1][2] She is best known for featuring alongside Jayam Ravi in Thillalangadi, with the director of the film recommending her to also star in Orange featuring Ram Charan Teja.', 0),
(153, 'R. Madhavan', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Madhavanprof.JPG/220px-Madhavanprof.JPG', 1, 'R. Madhavan (born 1 June 1970) is an Indian actor, writer, film producer and television host. Madhavan has received a Filmfare Award, an award from the Tamil Nadu State Film Awards alongside recognition and nominations from other organisations. He has been described as one of the few actors in India who is able to achieve pan-Indian appeal, appearing in films from seven different languages.[1][2]', 0),
(154, 'Arya (actor)', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/76/Arya_viewing_CCL_match%2C_India.jpg', 1, 'Arya (born as Jamshad on 11 December 1980) is an Indian film actor who mainly appears in Tamil films. He is best known for his roles in the films Pattiyal (2006), Naan Kadavul (2009), Arinthum Ariyamalum, Madrasapattinam (2010), Boss Engira Bhaskaran (2010) &amp; Vettai (2012).[1][2][3]', 0),
(155, 'Sameera Reddy', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a6/Sameera_Reddy_at_Mukti_Foundation_Event_%288%29_%28cropped%29.jpg/220px-Sameera_Reddy_at_Mukti_Foundation_Event_%288%29_%28cropped%29.jpg', 1, 'Sameera Reddy (Telugu:&#160;à°¸à°®à±€à°°à°¾ à°°à±†à°¡à±à°¡à°¿, SamÄ«rÄ Reá¸á¸i&#160;?; born 14 December 1982 is an Indian actress who primarily appears in Bollywood and Kollywood films. Apart from Hindi and Tamil, she has also appeared in a number of Telugu, Bengali and Malayalam films.', 0),
(156, 'Amala Paul', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/86/Amala-paul13.jpg/220px-Amala-paul13.jpg', 1, 'Amala Paul (born October 26, 1991) is an Indian film actress, who works primarily in the Tamil film industry. After appearing in supporting roles in a few low budget ventures, she received critical acclaim for the portrayal of a controversial character in the film, Sindhu Samaveli. Despite the failure of that film, Amala became noted after playing the title role in Mynaa, receiving critical acclaim for her work. Since then, she has been signed on for several notable projects and is considered the leading upcoming actress in Tamil films.[1]', 0),
(157, 'N. Linguswamy', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/9d/Lingusamy.jpg', 1, 'N. Linguswamy is an Indian film director, screenwriter and film producer, working primarily in Tamil cinema based in Chennai. He made his directorial debut with the family-drama Aanandham in 2001 and followed it up with the highly successful action films Run (2002), Sandakozhi (2005), Bheema (2008) and Paiyaa (2010). Vettai(2012)Tamil action film He and his brother Subash Chandrabose have also produced films through his production company, Thirupathi Brothers.', 0),
(158, 'Oviya', 'http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.20wmf3/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4', 1, 'Oviya (born April 29, 1991 as Helen Nelson) is an Indian model and film actress, who mainly works in the Tamil film industry. She rose to fame with the 2010 comedy film Kalavani.[1]', 0),
(159, 'Pandiraj', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png', 1, 'Pandiraj (Tamil: à®ªà®¾à®£à¯à®Ÿà®¿à®°à®¾à®œà¯) is Tamil film director from India. His debut movie, Pasanga (2009), was commercially successful[1] and won several awards, including the National Film Award for Best Dialogue. He worked as an assistant to director Cheran.', 0),
(160, 'Radhika Apte', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/83/Rakht_Charitra_Stills_-_Flickr_-_rgvzoomin_%282%29.jpg/220px-Rakht_Charitra_Stills_-_Flickr_-_rgvzoomin_%282%29.jpg', 1, 'Radhika Apte is an Indian film and stage actress.', 0),
