(222, 'Fahadh Faasil', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c1/Fahadh_Faasil.jpg/220px-Fahadh_Faasil.jpg', 1, 'Fahadh Faasil is an Indian film actor known for his work in Malayalam cinema. He made his debut in Kaiyethum Doorath (2001) directed by his father Fazil. After a sabbatical of nearly eight years, Fahadh had a resurrection of his career in the portmanteau film Kerala Cafe (2009). He earned critical acclaim for his performances in Chaappa Kurish (2011), Akam (2011), 22 Female Kottayam (2012) and Diamond Necklace (2012).', 0),
