(12, '\nShikari\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/bd/Shikari_2.jpg/220px-Shikari_2.jpg', 'The story revolves around a the life of a software engineer, who stumbles upon a novel called Shikari. He begins to read it and falls in love with a character from the book, which is set in the pre-Independence era. The story unfolds in two time-lines and both the actors play two characters each.[2]', '0000-00-00', 2, 1, 0),
(13, '\nOrange\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/7/76/Orange_%282010_film%29.jpg/220px-Orange_%282010_film%29.jpg', 'Yakobi (Kalabhavan Mani) is an orphan who works in a dairy farm, where he drives his own lorry on a contract basis. Orange is the name of his lorry. He falls in love with Saritha (Lena) and gets married. His sisters neither relatives did not know about this marriage. Later Saritha gave birth to babygirl Diya (Diya Babu ). Whenever he goes to his native place, his relatives enquire why he is still staying as a bachelor.', '0000-00-00', 2, 1, 0),
(14, '\nKarmayogi\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/2/26/Karmayogi_2011.jpg/220px-Karmayogi_2011.jpg', 'The film tells the story of Rudran Gurukkal, the lone male descendant of the Chathothu family. The family represents the Yogi community, in which Lord Shiva is believed to have been born. Rudran is haunted by a strange kind of destiny. This forms the crux of the story.[2]', '0000-00-00', 9, 1, 0),
(15, '\nThe King &amp; the Commissioner\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/a8/The-king-and-the-commissioner-poster.jpg/220px-The-king-and-the-comm', 'A Pakistan military group under Maj. Abdul Jalal Rana trespasses Indian waters targeting New Delhi. The plan is intercepted by Dr. Emma John of Intelligence Wing who informs it to her senior Padmabhushan Dr Sudarshan (Nedumudi Venu). Though Dr. Sudarshan tries to contact Home Minister, his Secretary (Sreekumar)snubs him by saying that its crazy to wake the minister up late at night and agrees for a meeting on the next morning. Dr Sudarshan offers Dr Emma a ride back home as it is too late for her to catch the metro train. Kishore Balakrishnan (Vijay Menon), the senior analyst at the agency, is', '0000-00-00', 11, 1, 0),
(16, '\nCobra\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/91/Cobra-malayalam-movie.jpg/220px-Cobra-malayalam-movie.jpg', 'This is first time Lal has directed a super-star film alone. Lal has produced some other Mammootty films like Hitler, Black, Thommanum Makkalum and Pothen Vava. Actor Lalu Alex had sang 4 lines of the song "Ente Nenjinullile".', '0000-00-00', 13, 1, 0),
(17, '\n\n\n\nThis article uses bare URLs for citations. Please consid', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a4/Text_document_with_red_question_mark.svg/40px-Text_document_wit', 'The filmtells a story with movie making as the backdrop. Vijayaraghavan appear as the title character of Josettan, who is a senior film producer. Anoop Menon comes up as Saajan Malyath; the still photographer of the movie who is accidentally selected to become the hero of the new movie on production.', '2012-04-20', 0, 1, 1),
(18, '\nMLA Mani: Patham Classum Gusthiyum\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/a8/MLA_Mani_Patham_Classum_Gusthiyum.jpg/220px-MLA_Mani_Patham_Classum_', 'All lyrics written by Murukan Kattakada,&#160;all music composed by Kalabhavan Mani[2].', '0000-00-00', 0, 1, 0),
(19, '\nDoctor Innocent aanu\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/d/d9/DoctorInnocentaanu.jpg/300px-DoctorInnocentaanu.jpg', 'Doctor Innocent aanu is the story of Homeopathic Doctor Bargavan Pillai(Innocent), who always helps poor patients. His wife Subha lakshmi (Sona Nair) wants to lead a posh life. She often finds time to interrupt into the affairs of her neighbours. She used a binocular to watch the neighbourhood. The doctor being a person of helping mentality put the family into debt. He starts a journey to find a solution to save his family from the crisis.', '0000-00-00', 0, 1, 0),
(20, '\nGrandmaster\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/6/65/GrandMaster_film.jpg', 'The film, produced by UTV Motion Pictures, released on 3 May 2012 and received mostly positive reviews from critics.[3] IBN Live called the film "a new phase in South Indian cinema".[4]', '0000-00-00', 14, 1, 0),
(21, '\nDiamond Necklace\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/eb/Diamond_Necklace_film.jpg/220px-Diamond_Necklace_film.jpg', 'It tells the story of a young high flying Oncologist working in Dubai. where we saw the low life of the working class in Dubai and here we see the razzle-dazzle of the rich that can starry-eyed youngsters.', '0000-00-00', 3, 1, 0),
(22, '\nArike\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/7/73/Arike.jpg/220px-Arike.jpg', 'The film tells the story of Shantanu (Dileep), a researcher in Linguistics, and his two friends, Kalpana (Samvritha) and Anuradha (Mamta). Anuradha is the sensitive type who has gone through certain bitter experiences in love. Kalpana is the more capricious one, who is changeable and loves being in love. Anuradha wants to play Cupid and bring Shantanu and Kalpana together; she knows that they care a lot for each other, but for some reason or the other are hesitant to take the next step.', '2012-05-18', 15, 1, 0),
(23, '\nAuto Shankar\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/b5/Auto_Shankar_Grand_100_Days_poster.jpg/220px-Auto_Shankar_Grand_100_', 'The movie was filmed in a variety of locations including Austria, the Bangalore Palace situated at Bangalore, Finland and the Mysore Lamps Factory, Mysore.[2]', '0000-00-00', 0, 1, 0),
(24, '\nParinayam\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png', 'Parinayam won 2 national awards (Best Screenplay and Best Film on Other Social Issues), also won several Kerala State Film Awards. This film deals with the mental and physical agony that a young Namboothiri widow had to undergo for losing her chastity. Parinayam was loosely based on Smarthavicharam of Kuryeddath Thathri, that created a shock among Kerala in early twentieth century that led to the reformation of Namboothiri community.', '0000-00-00', 17, 1, 0),
(25, 'Vaishali', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/0/09/Vaisali_VCD_Cover.jpg', 'Vaishali (Malayalam: à´µàµˆà´¶à´¾à´²à´¿) is a 1988 Malayalam film directed and edited by Bharathan.[1] Scripted by M. T. Vasudevan Nair, it was an adaptation of a sub-story told by Vedavyasa to King Yudhishtira in the epic Mahabharatha. It is the story of Vaishali, a devadasi girl who was assigned the mission of seducing Rishyashrungan, the son of Mahirshi Vibhandakan and bringing him to Chambapuri to perform a mahayagam to cause rain. Shot in a lavish setting, Vaishali was a huge hit at box office. This film, often considered as the best work of Bharathan is also considered as a cult classic ', '0000-00-00', 18, 1, 0),
(26, '\nKattathe Kilikkoodu\n', '', '', '0000-00-00', 18, 1, 1),
(27, '\nNirmala\n', '', 'The songs were composed by P. S. Divakar, a renowned saxophone player, and E. I. Warrier. Lyrics were by renowned poet G. Sankara Kurup. There were 15 songs in the film, sung by P. Leela, P. K. Raghavan, Sarojini Menon, T. K. Govindarao, Vasudeva Kurup and Vimala B Varma.[3] Govinda Rao and Sarojini Menon, who sang in this film, became the first male and female playback singers in Malayalam.[2]', '1948-02-25', 0, 1, 1),
(28, '\nOridathoru Phayalvaan\n(There Lived a Wrestler)\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/9/9d/Oridathoru_Phayalwan.jpg', 'It won the award for Best Script at the Kuala Lumpur International Film Festival,[1] and a Gold Medal at the Asian Film Festival.[2]', '0000-00-00', 19, 1, 0),
(29, '\nManjil Virinja Pookkal\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/0f/Manjil_Virinja_Pookkal.jpg/220px-Manjil_Virinja_Pookkal.jpg', 'Manjil Virinja Pookkal (Malayalam: à´®à´žàµà´žà´¿à´²àµâ€ à´µà´¿à´°à´¿à´žàµà´ž à´ªàµ‚à´•àµà´•à´³àµâ€, English: Flowers That Bloomed in the Mist) is a 1980 Malayalam film produced by Navodaya Appachan and directed by Fazil, starring Shankar, Poornima Jayaram, and Mohanlal in the main roles. This film was one of the biggest hits of the year and was a major landmark in the career of director Fazil. The songs were composed by Jerry Amaldev.', '0000-00-00', 20, 1, 0),
(30, '\nManichitrathazhu\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/4/43/Manichitrathazhu.jpg', 'The story is influenced from a tragedy that happened in Alummoottil Tharavadu, a famous central Travancore family, in the 19th century.[2] The film won the National Film Award for Best Popular Film Providing Wholesome Entertainment and Shobhana was awarded the National Film Award for Best Actress for her portrayal of the central character Ganga. The film also stars Mohanlal, Suresh Gopi, Nedumudi Venu, Innocent, Vinaya Prasad, K. P. A. C. Lalitha, Ganesh Kumar, and Thilakan in the main roles. The music was composed by M. G. Radhakrishnan.', '1993-12-25', 2, 1, 0),
(31, '\nKattu Vannu Vilichappol\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ee/Indian_Rupee_symbol.svg/7px-Indian_Rupee_symbol.svg.png', 'Seetha, born in an orthodox Hindu family, falls in love with the lower-caste Unni and later elopes with him to Bombay. Four years later, one day, Unni goes missing at Bombay. Seetha is pregnant and had to return to her native place. Through a newspaper report, Seetha comes to know that Unni has committed suicide after knowing he was infected with HIV. The heart-broken Seetha is isolated by the society and even by her parents who believe that she is also infected. Abu, a kind-hearted Muslim ferryman is her only help. Hated and isolated by the society, Abu and Seetha has to face lot of troubles.', '0000-00-00', 0, 1, 1),
(32, '\nLife Is Beautiful\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1e/Indiafilm.svg/30px-Indiafilm.svg.png', '', '0000-00-00', 20, 1, 1),
(33, '\nMeesa Madhavan\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/e/e8/Meesha_Madhavan.jpg', 'In 2003, this film was remade in Telugu as Dongodu starring Ravi Teja and Kalyani.[1]', '0000-00-00', 3, 1, 0),
(34, '\nSethurama Iyer CBI\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/2/2a/Sethurama_Iyer_CBI.gif', 'This film is the third in the series of the CBI investigative thrillers featuring Mammootty as CBI officer Sethurama Iyer. Prequels to this film are Oru CBI Diary Kurippu (1988) and Jagratha (1989). There was one sequel Nerariyan CBI (2005). A fifth sequel in the franchise has been announced and is now in the pre-production stage.[2]', '0000-00-00', 0, 1, 0),
(35, '\nRajamanikyam\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/2/23/Rajamanikyam_coverart.jpg/220px-Rajamanikyam_coverart.jpg', 'The star cast included Rahman, Manoj K Jayan, Cochin Haneefa, Ranjith, Salim Kumar, Saikumar, Bheeman Raghu, Sindhu Menon, and Padmapriya. The music is composed by Alex Paul with lyrics by Gireesh Puthenchery. The film was produced by Siraj Valiyaveettil under the banner of Valiyaveettil Movie International. It tells the story of Bellary Raja, alias Rajamanikyam, who tries to unite his warring siblings.', '0000-00-00', 24, 1, 0),
(36, '\nClassmates\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/2/29/Classmates_%28film%29.jpg', 'The story revolves around the college graduate class of 1992. In 2006, working in different corners of the world, the friends get together for a class reunion to revive the joy and laughter of their student days. Shockingly, on the night of the reunion, one of the classmates is almost murdered and goes into a coma.[5]', '0000-00-00', 3, 1, 0),
(37, 'Hello (disambiguation)', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fc/Padlock-silver.svg/20px-Padlock-silver.svg.png', 'Hello, with that spelling, was used in publications as early as 1833. These include an 1833 American book called The Sketches and Eccentricities of Col. David Crockett, of West Tennessee,[1] which was reprinted that same year in The London Literary Gazette.[2]', '0000-00-00', 0, 1, 1),
(38, '\nPazhassi Raja\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6d/Pazhassi_raja_2009.jpg/220px-Pazhassi_raja_2009.jpg', 'Originally filmed in Malayalam, Pazhassi Raja was dubbed in Tamil. The film was released on 16 October 2009 across Kerala with 130 prints.[4] Upon release, it enjoyed critical acclaim and huge box-office success collecting  1.53 crore on its opening day.[5] It was featured in international film festivals of Kerala and Mumbai besides many festivals across the world including the prestigious Fukuoka International Film Festival.', '0000-00-00', 17, 1, 0),
(39, '\n\n\n\nThis article does not cite any references or sources. Pl', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png', 'Jasmine Khan (Tabu) is the next door neighbour of Chandrashekar (Nedumudi Venu), a retired judge with a haunted past. The two become friends. Jasmine, a computer engineer, has to wear high power contact lenses because of her vision problems. She meets Vijay, a news reporter and the executive director of True Vision.', '0000-00-00', 2, 1, 0),
(40, 'Dadasaheb Phalke', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/53/Dada_Sahib_Film.gif/220px-Dada_Sahib_Film.gif', 'Dada Mohammed Sahib popularly called Dadasahib, is an old freedom fighter, and his son Abubacker is a former subeidar in the army. Abubacker is the brave son of a brave father, cannot help himself from reacting when he finds some terrorist activities and arms racket taking place in his own town Thaliyoor.', '0000-00-00', 26, 1, 0),
