(58, '\nMeghamalhar\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/ba/Meghamalhar_film.jpg/220px-Meghamalhar_film.jpg', 'The film tells the story of Rajeevan, an advocate and Nandita Menon, a writer. Rajeevan is married to Rekha, a bank employee, and has two kids. Nandita is married to Mukundan (Siddique), a businessman in the Gulf, and has a daughter. Both meet each other accidentally and in due course become intimate. Their tastes and thinking are almost alike. And in due course Nandita understands that Rajeevan is her long lost childmate and that makes the relationship mean much more for her. Rajeevan finds it much difficult to understand the nature of their relationship. But they continue with their sweet re', '0000-00-00', 34, 1, 0),
(59, '\nNaranathu Thampuran\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bc/Indiafilm.png/16px-Indiafilm.png', 'Production companies', '0000-00-00', 0, 1, 1),
(60, '\nNariman\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1e/Indiafilm.svg/30px-Indiafilm.svg.png', 'The film portrays an aggressive and belligerent police officer named Nariman who investigates a murder case for which an innocent man is falsely accused.', '0000-00-00', 36, 1, 1),
(61, '\nOne Man Show\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/58/One_Man_Show_%28film%29.jpg/220px-One_Man_Show_%28film%29.jpg', 'The story unfurls itself in the course of a TV game show, much akin to Who Wants to be a Millionaire. Jayakrishnan (Jayaram), the protagonist, comes to take part in the show, hosted by popular filmstar Mukesh. In the course of the show, the host pries into Jayakrishnanâ€™s past and the whole story is unfurled in flashback.', '0000-00-00', 37, 1, 0),
(62, 'Romanian', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/8/8f/Praja.jpg/220px-Praja.jpg', 'Praja is a 2001 Malayalam film by Joshiy starring Mohanlal, N. F. Varghese, Cochin Haneefa and Aishwarya. The film was produced by Joshiy and Renji Panicker under the banner of Mukhyadhara Films. Despite the huge star cast, big budget and heavy initial pull, "praja" - blockbuster of the year.', '0000-00-00', 38, 1, 0),
(63, '\nRandam Bhavam\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/d/dd/Randaam_Bhavam.jpg/220px-Randaam_Bhavam.jpg', 'The film begins with Police Officer Jeevan(Biju Menon) taking charge of Mangalore city Police. He learns from his suboridinate Sudhakaran Nair that the city is still ruled by underworld don Govindji (Thilakan). Jeevan reveals that he has lived in Managalore as a child.', '0000-00-00', 3, 1, 0),
