(73, '\n\n\n\nThis article does not cite any references or sources. Pl', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png', 'Nakshathrakkannulla Rajakumaran Avanundoru Rajakumari revolves around a family that claims that they are the descendants of the brave chekavars, who were the warriors of the Vadakkanpaattu. Bhageerathi Amma (K.R.Vijaya) has two sons, Veerabhadra Kurup (Narendra Prasad) and Kochchukurup (Kalabhavan Kurup), and a daughter Subhadra, who constantly feud with each other. The elder Kurupâ€™s daughter Aswathy (Gayathri Raghuram) is in love with her muracherukkan, Subhadraâ€™s son Ananthu (Prithviraj), but their parents object to the match. They are encouraged by Chandutty (Jagathy Sreekumar), Bhaskar', '2002-09-13', 27, 1, 1),
