(119, '\nOrdinary (film)\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/9b/Ordinary_film.jpg/220px-Ordinary_film.jpg', 'The film follows the adventures of a K.S.R.T.C. bus that travels from Pathanamthitta to the village of Gavi. It received positive critical reviews and turned out to be the first blockbuster film of 2012 in Malayalam cinema.[5]', '0000-00-00', 95, 1, 0),
(120, '\nThe King &amp; the Commissionel\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/a8/The-king-and-the-commissioner-poster.jpg/220px-The-king-and-the-comm', 'A Pakistan military group under Maj. Abdul Jalal Rana trespasses Indian waters targeting New Delhi. The plan is intercepted by Dr. Emma John of Intelligence Wing who informs it to her senior Padmabhushan Dr Sudarshan (Nedumudi Venu). Though Dr. Sudarshan tries to contact Home Minister, his Secretary (Sreekumar)snubs him by saying that its crazy to wake the minister up late at night and agrees for a meeting on the next morning. Dr Sudarshan offers Dr Emma a ride back home as it is too late for her to catch the metro train. Kishore Balakrishnan (Vijay Menon), the senior analyst at the agency, is', '2012-03-23', 11, 1, 0),
(121, '\n\n\n\nThis article uses bare URLs for citations. Please consid', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a4/Text_document_with_red_question_mark.svg/40px-Text_document_wit', 'The film tells a story with movie making as the backdrop. Vijayaraghavan appear as the title character of Josettan, who is a senior film producer. Anoop Menon comes up as Saajan Malyath; the still photographer of the movie who is accidentally selected to become the hero of the new movie on production.', '2012-04-20', 0, 1, 1),
(122, 'Pokkiri Raja', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/2/23/Pokkiri_Raja.jpg/220px-Pokkiri_Raja.jpg', 'The film revolves around Madhavan Nair who unknowingly kills a teenager and his eldest son. Raja takes the blame and is sentenced to jail for five years. After returning from jail, Raja moves to Madurai and there he rescues the life of the daughter of Maniannai, the village land lord and then Raja turns his right hand and he is named as Madurai Raja. Years later, he started being known as Pokkiri Raja.', '2010-05-07', 2, 1, 0),
(123, '\nRaamanam\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/41/Flag_of_India.svg/22px-Flag_of_India.svg.png', 'The movie is a re-depiction of Smarakasilakal, a celebrated Malayalam novel by Punathil Kunhabdulla.[1][2]', '0000-00-00', 2, 1, 1),
(124, '\nKerala Cafe\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/2/2a/Kerala_Cafe.jpg/220px-Kerala_Cafe.jpg', 'Backwater Media &amp; Entertainment Private Limited distributed the film. The film released in Kerala on 29 October 2009.', '2009-10-09', 22, 1, 0),
(125, '\nRitu\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/02/Ritu_poster.jpg/220px-Ritu_poster.jpg', 'Ritu is about young people working in the IT sector. The story follows the lives of three childhood friends: Sunny Immatty (Asif Ali), Sarath Varma (Nishan), Varsha John (Rima). The trio were almost inseparable as friends; they grew up in the same neighborhood in their love, bonding and innocence. They shared a dream of journeying together in life forever.', '0000-00-00', 15, 1, 0);
