(174, '\nSaguni\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/5/51/Saguni.JPG', 'The film was first revealed in early April 2011, when it was reported that Karthi was considering a "social satire" script written by debutant film maker, Shankar Dayal, to be his next venture after the success of his previous film Siruthai.[2] Karthi confirmed the news and revealed he would feature in a new get-up for the film, although expressing that the script was still in development.[3][4] Veteran actress Raadhika Sarathkumar signed on to play a supporting role in May 2011[5], whilst Roja signed on to play a doctor in the film and Mumtaj was selected to play a role making her comeback af', '2012-06-22', 0, 2, 0),
(175, 'Mayavi (1965 film)', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/5b/Mayavi_%28film%29.jpg/220px-Mayavi_%28film%29.jpg', 'There are two songs in the film, scored by Alex Paul and lyrics penned by Vayalar Sharath Chandra Varma.', '0000-00-00', 119, 1, 0),
(176, '\nVinodayathra\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/9d/Vinodayathra.jpg/220px-Vinodayathra.jpg', 'It is the story of a good natured but irresponsible young man, Vinod (Dileep) who comes to a hilly village live with his elder sister Vimala (Seetha) and brother in law, shaji (Mukesh). Shaji is an engineer and Vinod wants to learn life from him, but end up creating problems for Shaji.', '0000-00-00', 2, 1, 0),
(177, '\nChotta Mumbai\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/48/Chotta_Mumbai.jpg/220px-Chotta_Mumbai.jpg', 'The film starts in a street in Fort Kochi where Vasco da Gama (Mohanlal), the son of a wrestler named Michael (Saikumar), lives. Vasco and his gang of five â€” Chandrappan (Siddique), Susheelan (Bijukuttan), Sainu (Manikuttan), Basheer (Jagathy Sreekumar) and cousin Tomichchan (Indrajith) are small-time goondas, involved in petty offences and as the movie progresses, these characters turn out to be more endearing than bad.', '0000-00-00', 60, 1, 0),
