(186, '\nHappy\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f6/Happy_cover.jpg', 'Upon release, the film was dubbed into Malayalam and released with the title Happy be Happy. The Telugu version was moderately successful at the box office whereas the Malayalam version was a smash hit collecting Rs 4.22 lakhs in its opening week at Ernakulam. The film was remade in Bengali under the title Bolo Na Tumi Amar starring Dev and Koyel and in Oriya under the title Loafer starring Babushan and Archita Sahu.', '2006-01-27', 220, 1, 0),
(188, '\n\n\n\nThis article uses bare URLs for citations. Please consid', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a4/Text_document_with_red_question_mark.svg/40px-Text_document_wit', 'The film tells a story with movie making as the backdrop. Vijayaraghavan appear as the title character of Josettan, who is a senior film producer. Anoop Menon comes up as Saajan Malyath; the still photographer of the movie who is accidentally selected to become the hero of the new movie on production.', '2012-04-20', 0, 1, 0),
(187, '\nOrdinary\n', 'http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/9b/Ordinary_film.jpg/220px-Ordinary_film.jpg', 'The film follows the adventures of a K.S.R.T.C. bus that travels from Pathanamthitta to the village of Gavi. It received positive critical reviews and turned out to be the first blockbuster film of 2012 in Malayalam cinema.[5]', '2012-03-17', 95, 1, 0),
